message.en_US: May I interest you in an explanation of new modifiers/mechanics?
\c[3]Overhealing\c[0] refers to the ability to heal beyond your normal maximum HP.
There are two primary methods of being able to \c[3]overheal\c[0] - through a \c[3]modifier\c[0], or \c[3]special food items\c[0].
The modifier \i[stat-el-overheal] Overheal allows the user to heal up to the modifier's percentage beyond their max HP through normal means.
This includes nearly all methods of healing - including but not limited to consumables and certain combat arts - though at 1/4 efficiency.
However it should be noted that standard HP regeneration \c[1]will not function beyond 100% HP\c[0].
As for the other method of overhealing - certain consumables allow for overhealing up to a certain value.
These consumables will work at full effectiveness up to their intended overheal max HP, and are able to go beyond with the aid of the Overheal modifier.
Unlike normal consumables - going beyond their intended value will merely have 1/2 effectiveness compared to the standard 1/4.
When one is beyond 100% HP, one will notice their HP bar changes color to accommodate the extra health.
Do you have any other questions?
